ly cause. The book offers scholars and policymakers a full analysis of the legal and policy issues under debate, and it brings into sharp focus the impact of preemption on the lives of people involved in actual lawsuits. McGarity highlights the arguments for and against preemption and suggests guidelines for resolving difficult issues in a variety of contexts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aExclusive and concurrent legislative powerszUnited States. 0aFederal governmentzUnited States. 0aJudicial reviewzUnited States. 0aPolitical questions and judicial powerzUnited States. 7aLAW / Government / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030012296140uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030015220340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300152203423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300152203/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY